Ex 6

library(MASS)
library(glmnet)
# (a) 100 observations from 100-d mvnormal dist, stored in matrix X of covariates
set.seed(1)
n <- 100
p <- 100

X <- mvrnorm(n, mu = rep(0,p), Sigma = diag(p))

#(b) generate y 
eps <- rnorm(n,mean = 0, sd = sqrt(0.1))
y <- rowSums(X[,1:10]) + eps

#(c) lasso and ridge
lasso_model <- glmnet(X,y, intercept = TRUE, alpha = 1)
ridge_model <- glmnet(X,y, intercept = TRUE, alpha = 0)

#(d) plots

par(mfrow = c(1,2), mgp = c(2,0.5,0), cex = .7 )
plot(lasso_model, main = "Lasso model")
plot(lasso_model, xvar = "lambda", main = "Lasso with Lambda")

plot(ridge_model, main = "Ridge model")
plot(ridge_model, xvar = "lambda", main = "Ridge with Lambda")

#(e) non-zero coefficients  at each lambda
lasso_nonzero <- sapply(predict(lasso_model, type = "nonzero"), length)
ridge_nonzero <- sapply(predict(ridge_model, type = "nonzero"), length)

lasso_deviance <- deviance(lasso_model)
ridge_deviance <- deviance(ridge_model)

par(mfrow = c(1,2), mgp = c(2,0.5,0), cex = .7 )

plot(lasso_model$lambda, lasso_nonzero, type = "b", log = "x", 
     xlab = "lambda", ylab = "Number of Non-Zero Coefficients", 
     main = "Lasso model, Non-Zero Coefficients", col = "blue")

plot(ridge_model$lambda, ridge_nonzero, type = "b", log = "x", 
     xlab = "lambda", ylab = "Number of Non-Zero Coefficients", 
     main = "Ridge model,Non-Zero Coefficients", col = "red")

# Plot the deviance (RSS) for Lasso and Ridge

plot(lasso_model$lambda, lasso_deviance, type = "b", log = "x", 
     xlab = "lambda", ylab = "Deviance or RSS", 
     main = "Lasso: Deviance vs Lambda", col = "blue")

plot(ridge_model$lambda, ridge_deviance, type = "b", log = "x", 
     xlab = "lambda", ylab = "Deviance or RSS", 
     main = "Ridge: Deviance vs Lambda", col = "red")

original<-icu_df$sta
decision_b<-function(fitv,fito){
  res<-c()
  for (i in seq(0.001,1,0.001)) {
    v <- fitv>i
    r<-sum(abs(v-fitv))
    res[length(res)+1]<-r
  }
  vec <- fitv>which.min(res)/1000
  return(c(which.min(res)/1000,sum(abs(vec-fito))/length(fito)))
}
# Optimal decision boundary and misspecification
decision_b(fitted(model2),original)
## [1] 0.484 0.135
decision_b(fitted(aic_model),original)
## [1] 0.485 0.150
decision_b(fitted(bic_model),original)
## [1] 0.453 0.170

#(b)
set.seed(2)

train_index <- sample(1:nrow(Default), nrow(Default)/2)
train_data <- Default[train_index,]
test_data <- Default[-train_index,]


logit_model <- glm(default ~ income + balance, data = train_data,
                   family = binomial(link = "logit"))

threshold <- 0.5
y_pred_test <- predict(logit_model, test_data, type = "response")
y_pred_test <- ifelse(y_pred_test > threshold, 1, 0)


res_1 <- data.frame(prop_defaults=numeric(1), misc_error=numeric(1), false_neg=numeric(1))
res_1$prop_defaults[1] <- length(which(test_data$default==1)) / nrow(test_data)
res_1$misc_error[1] <- sum(y_pred_test != test_data$default) / nrow(test_data)
res_1$false_neg[1] <- sum(test_data$default[which(y_pred_test == 0)] == 1) / nrow(test_data)

#(c)
set.seed(3)

n <- 100
res_2 <- data.frame(prop_defaults=numeric(n), misc_error=numeric(n), false_neg=numeric(n))

for(i in 1:n) {
  train_index <- sample(1:nrow(Default), nrow(Default) / 2)
  train_data <- Default[train_index, ]
  test_data <- Default[-train_index, ]
  
  logit_model <- glm(default ~ income + balance,
                     data = train_data,
                     family = binomial(link = "logit"))
  threshold <- 0.5
  y_pred_test <- predict(logit_model, test_data, type = "response")
  y_pred_test <- ifelse(y_pred_test > threshold, 1, 0)
 
  res_2$prop_defaults[i] <- length(which(test_data$default==1)) / nrow(test_data)
  res_2$misc_error[i] <- sum(y_pred_test != test_data$default) / nrow(test_data)
  res_2$false_neg[i] <- sum(test_data$default[which(y_pred_test == 0)] == 1) / nrow(test_data)
}
  
par(mfrow = c(1, 2))
attach(res_2)

# Validation Set Error vs. Proportion of Defaults
plot(prop_defaults, misc_error,
     col = "red", pch = 19,
     xlab = "Proportion of defaults (test set)",
     ylab = "Misclassification error")

# False Negative Rate vs. Proportion of Defaults
plot(prop_defaults, false_neg,
     col = "blue", pch = 19,
     xlab = "Proportion of defaults (test set)",
     ylab = "False negative rate")

detach("res_2")
